<h1 class="pagetitle">Sync Device</h1>
<br><br><div class="column1-unit-pages">
<h1>Introduction</h1>
<p>In order to upload <i>eRounds</i> from the Mesa mobile device to your desktop you must first sync the device with your computer. This is done using a program which is readily available via the <i>Software Distribution</i> website. Follow the steps below to sync your mobile device with your computer.</p>
<br><br></div><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><div class="column1-unit-pages"><br><br>
<h1 id="desktop-setup">Desktop Setup</h1>
<p>In <a href=" http://gss.rl.gov/softdist/beforetxt.asp?path=winsys\\activsync\\msas45\\&nai=msas45a.na&app=ActiveSync+4%2E5+%2F+Mobile+Device+Center+6 " target="_blank"><i>Software Distribution</i></a> search for "ActiveSync." Download and install <i>ActiveSync4.5/Mobile Device Center 6</i>. When the program is installed and ran for the first time it will look like the screenshot to the left.</p>
<img class="desktop-prtscr-img" src="img/sync-device/active_sync.png" alt="" />
<br></div>
<br><br><div class="column1-unit-pages">
<p>After the application has been installed there are necessary steps to be completed for both the Windows Mobile desktop application and the Mesa mobile device.</p>
<br><br></div><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><div class="column1-unit-pages"><br><br>
<h1>Windows Mobile Interface</h1>
<ul type="square">
<li>Open the <i>Windows Mobile</i> application</li>
<li>Select the option "Connect without setting up your device"</li>
</ul>
<img class="desktop-prtscr-img" src="img/sync-device/active_sync2.png" alt="" />
<br><br></div><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><hr class="clear-contentunit-pages" /><div class="column1-unit-pages"><br><br>
